Cell.Text: Yes, yes, so you said. But so what? The end is upon us. I may as well die here as anywhere else. I'm tired of running.

Node.Caption: MQ202EsbernOutroA1: The Thalmor have found you. We have to get out of here.

Cell.Text: <<Shared>> Haven't you figured it out yet? What more needs to happen before you all wake up and see what's going on?

Node.Caption: MQ202EsbernOutroA2: What do you mean, "the end is upon us"?

Cell.Text: <<Shared>> Yes! Yes! You see, you know but you refuse to understand!

Node.Caption: MQ202EsbernOutroExclusiveB1: Alduin... the dragon who's raising the others?

Cell.Text: [S] Oh, yes. It's all been foretold. The end has begun. Alduin has returned. | Only a Dragonborn can stop him. But no Dragonborn has been known for centuries. | It seems that the gods have grown tired of us. They've left us to our fate, as the plaything of Alduin the World-Eater.

[S] GS|Fine! I'll just... leave the rest of it. Let's go, then, if you're in such a hurry.
G|Come in, come in. Mustn't speak of these things in the Ratway.
You... Dragonborn? Is it really true?
So Delphine keeps up the fight, after all these years. | I thought she'd have realized it's hopeless by now. I tried to tell her, years ago...

<<Shared>> Alduin has returned, just like the prophecy said! | The Dragon from the dawn of time, who devours the souls of the dead! | No one can escape his hunger, here or in the afterlife! Alduin will devour all things and the world will end. Nothing can stop him!
You're right, I forget myself. I've lived without hope for so long... | The prophecies are clear. Only the Dragonborn can stop Alduin.
What? You're... can it really be true? Dragonborn? | Then... there is hope! The gods have not abandoned us! We must... we must...

Node.Caption: MQ202EsbernOutroExclusiveEndTopic: It's not hopeless, Esbern. I'm Dragonborn.

Cell.Text: Important? Far more than even she realizes! If you are Dragonborn, then...

Node.Caption: MQ202EsbernOutroB1: Yes. Delphine seemed to think it was important.

Cell.Text: Then... there is hope after all. For so long, all I could do was watch our doom approach, helplessly.
